recursive vs iterative:

- readability: recursive better
- space complexity: iterative is O(1), faster than recursive -> memory efficient; recursion creates more mem. due to the call stack
- recursion: more overhead due to function calls; iteration: no overhead from func calls (only for/while loops)
- recursion: more mathy and elegant code; iteration: easier to debug (printing and tracing)
- recursion: suitable for probs that can be BROKEN DOWN into subprobs (sorting) or trying all possibilities (BACKTRACKING)/ DIVIDE AND CONQUER;
iteration: suitable for sequential operations


