1. Bubble sort: simplest sorting algorithm:
- traverse from left, compare adjacent elements and the higher one placed on the right -> largest ele move to the right end at first
- process goes on for second largest -> ends when array is sorted (swapping 2 adjacent ones at a time)

-> O(n^2) time - 2 nested loops, and O(1) space

2. Merge sort:
- divide array into 2 halves -> sort each half -> merge the sorted halves back tgt
-> the dividing then sorting (merging) process is repeated till array is sorted
- process: have 2 ptrs for 2 arrays; compare 2 eles (pointed to by 2 ptrs, at the beginning of 2 arrays)-> put the smaller ele in the res array and increment ptr

-> O(nlogn) time and O(n) space

3. Quick sort:
- eles divided into subarrays by picking a pivot ele; position the pivot ele in such a way: eles smaller than pivot ele is to its left, eles greater than pivot 
is to its right
- the left and right arrays are divided -> sorted using the same method till each array has 1 ele left -> everything is sorted -> combine them

-> implement this later
Time: O(nlogn), worst: O(n^2), space: O(1)

